<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2491/130A.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Minister for Foreign Affairs of Costa
                                    Rica</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-18"><hi rend="italic">March 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The convention of arbitration was signed last evening by the
                            representatives of Costa Rica and Panama. I congratulate you and your
                            Government most cordially upon this honorable and satisfactory solution
                            of an old and troublesome question.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>